#Reliance Jio launches #JioAirFiber with plans starting at Rs 599. JioAirFiber is India's latest home entertainment and Wi-Fi service.  Jio Announces Launch of JioAirFiber  #JioAirFiber goes live in 8 cities in India, Ahmedabad, Bengaluru, Chennai, Delhi, Hyderabad, Kolkata, Mumbai and Pune on the auspicious occasion of Ganesh Chaturthi   This Jio AirFiber Max plan comes with a validity of 30 days and is priced at Rs 1,499. Subscribers will get 300 Mbps speed and access to 550+ TV channels along with 14 OTT apps like Disney+ Hotstar, JioCinema, Sony Liv, and more. Under this plan, buyers will get 500 Mbps speed with a validity of 30 days  Now available.  jio.com/airfiber

Walt Disney is holding initial talks with potential buyers for its India streaming and television business including Mukesh Ambani's Reliance Industries, as per people associated with the matter. The US-based entertainment giant is discussing options with various buyers - from a deal for the complete Disney Star business to a piecemeal trade including a mix of its assets including sports rights and regional streaming service Disney+ Hotstar.
